Job Description:
- Execute the recruitment process for assigned positions and support the onboarding of new employees and interns. This includes, but is not limited to: initiating recruitment requests, sourcing and screening applications for both full-time and internship roles, conducting interviews and candidate selection, negotiating and managing offers with candidates, etc.;
- Input and manage HR data as required by management and within the scope of assigned responsibilities. Maintain and update the HR database efficiently;
- Responsible for the process of signing training and probationary contracts;
- Handle administrative procedures related to the signing of labor contracts, resignation process;
- Carry out recruitment activities using the Workday HR system, ensuring all recruitment information is accurately and promptly updated;
- Participate in organizing employer branding activities such as career fairs, promotional events, community outreach, and company tours;
- Address employee inquiries related to HR matters within the scope of assigned duties;
- Prepare periodic and ad-hoc reports as required;
- Participate in departmental and company-wide activities and projects;
- Perform other tasks as assigned.

Job Requirements:
- Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Finance, Business Administration, or related field;
- Formal Qualifications: at least a year of experience in recruiting; Experience in mass recruitment is a plus;
- A board understanding of recruiting process, talent acquisition activities and the ways of approaching and utilizing potential candidate resources;
- Good at Excel skill; Experience in Automate is preferred;
- Have experience in related HR systems or software. Proficient with Microsoft Office Suite or related software;
- Good communication skills in both English and Vietnamese; English level (CEFR) B1+ or equivalent;
- Highly responsible, hard-working, can work under pressure and deadline;
- Must be flexible on work schedule based on the recruitment activity requirements and success pattern.

